3132 PART B
34 Sec. B-1. Carrying provision; Department of Secretary of State,
35 Administration - Motor Vehicles program. Notwithstanding any provision of law to
36 the contrary, the State Controller shall carry forward up to $9,000,000 in the All Other line
37 category in the Department of Secretary of State, Administration - Motor Vehicles
38 program, after all financial commitments for obligations and budgetary adjustments have
39 been made, at the end of fiscal year 2024-25 to the next fiscal year to the All Other line
40 category in the Department of Secretary of State, Administration - Motor Vehicles
41 program, of which up to $2,000,000 must be used for the Bureau of Motor Vehicles
42 modernization project and up to $7,000,000 must be used for the new license plate general
43 issue project. These funds were previously authorized to be carried forward in Public Law
44 2023, chapter 50, Part B.
Page 4 - 132LR2410(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 179, L.D. 275
1 PART C
2 Sec. C-1. Carrying provision; Department of Secretary of State,
3 Administration - Motor Vehicles program. Notwithstanding any provision of law
4 to the contrary, the State Controller shall carry forward up to $2,500,000 in unexpended
5 balances in the Personal Services and All Other line categories in the Department of
6 Secretary of State, Administration - Motor Vehicles program, after all financial
7 commitments for obligations and budgetary adjustments have been made, at the end of
8 fiscal year 2024-25 to the All Other line category in the Department of Secretary of State,
9 Administration - Motor Vehicles program. These funds must be used to continue the
10 modernization of systems and services at the Bureau of Motor Vehicles.'
11 Amend the bill by adding before the summary the following:
12 'Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
13 takes effect when approved.'
14 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
15 number to read consecutively.
16 SUMMARY
1177 PART A
18 This Part makes appropriations and allocations of funds for fiscal year 2024-25.
19 PART B
20 This Part directs that funds carry forward into fiscal year 2025-26 for the Department
21 of the Secretary of State, which extends the time within which previously authorized funds
22 may be used in accommodation of the plate manufacturing billing process.
23 PART C
24 This Part directs the State Controller to carry forward up to $2,500,000 in unexpended
25 balances in the Personal Services and All Other line categories in the Department of
26 Secretary of State, Administration - Motor Vehicles program, after all financial
27 commitments for obligations and budgetary adjustments have been made, at the end of
28 fiscal year 2024-25 to the next fiscal year to the All Other line category in the Department
29 of Secretary of State, Administration - Motor Vehicles program. These funds must be used
30 to continue the modernization of systems and services at the Bureau of Motor Vehicles.
